Open edges:
- Partial-line reflow remains intentionally deferred; the current model reflows explicit logical blocks instead of trying to mutate only overflowing physical lines.
- Hash-prefixed shell comments are still not specially distinguished from markdown-style headings. If that matters later, detection should likely be filetype-aware instead of broadening prefix heuristics again.
- Context inheritance currently looks upward only; extend with evidence if downward context becomes necessary in real use.
